      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 135: This fallback assumes openServiceTunnel returns a synchronous status where an empty string means \"failed to open\". If the adapter returns a tunnel id immediately (i.e. the request is queued and the connection/port-bind happens asynchronously), then: (a) a busy preferred port will NOT produce an empty return, so the OS-assigned fallback here never fires, and (b) if it does return a non-empty id, a later async bind failure leaves a broken pending entry with no error flagged. Conversely, if the first call already registered a tunnel and then returns \"\", the retry with port 0 could open a second tunnel. Please confirm openServiceTunnel\u0027s contract; if the port-busy condition is only known asynchronously, drive the fallback from the adapter\u0027s tunnel-status signal rather than from the return value.",
