      "side": 1,
      "message": "[info] Line 167: preferredPort is represented as a numeric quint16 on the peer path (sanitizePreferredPort in sharedservicesadapter.cpp) but as a string on the local path (\"0\"/servicePort in SharedServiceDialog). The `!\u003d\u003d \"0\"` string comparison here only works because local getSharedServices stores strings; if this delegate ever received the numeric form, `0 !\u003d\u003d \"0\"` would be true and a 0 port could leak through (only saved by the falsy short-circuit). Normalize with Number() for robustness and consistency: `(Number(modelData.preferredPort) \u003e 0) ? modelData.preferredPort : \"\"`.",
      "revId": "bb41a603353a2df92cd2f3a1ceba37eda6bea19f",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
