      "message": "[info] Line 370: `parent: parent` is redundant and confusing: a Popup already defaults its parent to the item it is declared in (the NewIconButton), so this binding is a no-op that reads as self-assignment. Additionally, `visible: false` (line 377) is a declarative binding on a property that Popup manages imperatively via open()/close(); relying on open() to break the binding is fragile, and the `opacity: visible ? 1.0 : 0.0` fade-out will be skipped because close() flips visible to false instantly. Prefer removing `parent: parent` and driving open state through open()/close() only.",
